summary: DT:  CONTACT STATED THAT ONE SIDE OF THE FRAME ON  MOTORCYCLE WAS LONGER THAN THE OTHER SIDE. THIS CAUSED THE MOTORCYCLE DRIVE TO THE RIGHT.  DEALER GETS THE FRAME FROM CHINA AND IS ALSO THE MANUFACTURER. DEALER HAS TAKEN THE FRAME BACK, BUT CONTACT DID NOT WANT ANOTHER FRAME FROM CHINA.  MOTORCYCLE  A 2003 HURRICANE FAT DADDY. MANUFACTURER AND DEALER ARE AT SAME ADDRESS AS DEALER. MOTORCYCLE HAS NEVER BEEN REGISTERED.  *AK
